  <br/>
  <div id="container" class="instructions" style="display: none;">
    
    <div class="content" id="main_content">
      <p>
        <i>Inspired by a lesson on the nature of deques</i>
      </p>
      
      <p class="small">
        Instructions: <br/>
        Output the requested stream of numbers in the order that they appear from left to right by using a deque to push and pop values. Values must be pushed into deque in numerical order.
      </p>
      
      <p class="small">
        For example, if the requested order is <b>1 4 3 2 5</b>, I would take the following steps to solve the problem: <br/>
        <ol>
          <li>Push <b>1</b> <i>(I have no other choice)</i></li>
          <li>Pop <b>1</b> <i>(Since <b>1</b> is a number we want in the output <b>now</b>, let us pop it)</i></li>
          <li>Push <b>2</b> <i>(I cannot push 4 because then next number after <b>1</b> is <b>2</b>)</i></li>
          <li>Push <b>3</b></li>
          <li>Push <b>4</b></li>
          <li>Pop <b>4</b></li>
          <li>Pop <b>3</b></li>
          <li>Pop <b>2</b></li>
          <li>Push <b>5</b></li>
          <li>Pop <b>5</b></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p>
        <a href="http://dribbble.com/players/ivan">Theme</a>
      </p>
      
